Proposal 92924 is a policy proposal for a sound money standard

The details of this one are to draft a policy proposal for Canada to return to a sound money standard

Outline a clear purpose, emphasize the problem of unchecked currency inflation without backing with real commodities, and propose a clear policy to back the Canadian dollar with the treasury of hard assets held in a network of military secured vaults

That last part probably doesn't have to be in there. That's more semantics and details

But essentially the action there is, is it worth drafting a document to be able to send politicians and to be able to have as a resource for Canadians to actually see? I think lots of details to be determined

What are the hard assets? How and why are they chosen? There's lots of elements there

I don't even know if the actual assets themselves necessarily need to be included in the first version of the policy proposal

The point of this proposal, which I actually put in there, was that we need something real and tangible to actually lock into

If we believe that fixing the money is going to fix Canada, what does fixing the money actually mean? 

My take is that the first step in fixing the money is to create guardrails that limit the ability to print money without any restraint

I think having some sort of backing, I don't know if it's a basket of hard assets or whatever it might be, Canada clearly has a competitive advantage in certain hard assets, gold, Bitcoin due to energy, uranium

We have this abundant resource landscape and I think there just has to be, number one, an understanding that that's important and number two, that there is actually a way to tether dollars to some sort of treasury of assets

