And it's about refining clear selection criteria for orange politicians that we support. And in thinking about this, the idea of an oath came to mind

Because instead of writing down all these different qualities of a politician we want to support, I think frankly, the selection criteria can be extremely simple

If we have a clear, explicit oath, a set of sentences that someone has to agree with to really be considered someone who's aligned, it can serve as a very simple self-selection criteria

It can also serve as an accurate measure of whether someone deserves to be supported by the orange party

The inspiration partially came from the notion of the Hippocratic Oath, which debatable how much utility that has now or how impactful it is now in the world of modern medicine

But historically, the Hippocratic Oath was an ethical oath for doctors to uphold ethical standards

And to me, regardless of whether it's called the Orange Oath or Satoshiocratic Oath was another word that was floated out on NOSTR by a member, that oath can serve as an ethical oath for politicians to uphold ethical governance

And so it can be sort of a parallel to the Hippocratic Oath. And I'm just going to go in to the repo.

There's an Orange Oath section. There's a version 1.1 posted in there, which will be continuously updated

There's also a discussion that I'm going to have with another member about the distinction between an oath and a prayer and the distinction there

And, you know, I don't know if this has to be this rigid thing, but I think having a template is helpful

Version 1.1 of the Orange Oath is: 

"I solemnly swear by my life and my love of it that I will relentlessly expose the theft of currency inflation, teaching about its erosion of wealth and liberty

I vow to restore and fiercely defend a sound money standard rooted in truth so that current and future Canadians may live freely with abundance"

That's probably a bit wordier than it needs to be, but the crux of it is two portions

First one, I swear to expose the theft of currency inflation and teach about the erosion of wealth and liberty that it has

And the second part is a vow to restore, first restore, and then fiercely defend a sound money standard rooted in truth

Now, where does this become useful when selecting politicians? Well, the simple way is you give that to a politician. You say, do you agree and stand by this?

